casebody.data:
STATE of Iowa, Plaintiff-Appellee,
v.
Douglas Kent SMITH, Defendant-Appellant. No. 18-0329 Court of Appeals of Iowa. Filed January 9, 2019

DECISION WITHOUT PUBLISHED OPINION See Iowa R. App. P. 6.904

The defendant asserts his trial counsel provided ineffective assistance by allowing the defendant to plead guilty to operating while intoxicated, third or subsequent offense, without a factual basis to support the plea. AFFIRMED.

AFFIRMED.
